abstract: As some inside and outside the White House call for weakening China’s links to U.S. financial markets, e-commerce giant Alibaba is considering listing its shares in Hong Kong.
snippet: As some inside and outside the White House call for weakening China’s links to U.S. financial markets, e-commerce giant Alibaba is considering listing its shares in Hong Kong.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — President Trump’s trade war with China has prompted a broad rethinking of how the two economies have become so intertwined, leading some manufacturers to trim supply chains in China and American authorities to start cutting off crucial technology for Chinese companies.

abstract: An inflexible agenda and a global retreat.
snippet: An inflexible agenda and a global retreat.
lead_paragraph: In Australia a week ago, the party of the left lost an election it was supposed to win, to a conservative government headed by an evangelical Christian who won working-class votes by opposing liberal climate policies. In India last week, the Hindu-nationalist prime minister, Narendra Modi, won an overwhelming electoral victory. And as of this writing, Europeans are electing a Parliament that promises to have more populist representation than before.

abstract: In response to criticism, the company said it would waive performance-pay reductions for 12 months for athletes “who decide to have a baby.”
snippet: In response to criticism, the company said it would waive performance-pay reductions for 12 months for athletes “who decide to have a baby.”
lead_paragraph: Responding to criticism about its treatment of its sponsored athletes who become pregnant, the sportswear giant Nike committed on Friday to ensuring that such athletes are not financially penalized.

abstract: The Trump administration announced an aid package for farmers on Thursday to mollify an important political constituency hurt by a trade clash with China.
snippet: The Trump administration announced an aid package for farmers on Thursday to mollify an important political constituency hurt by a trade clash with China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Thursday unveiled a $16 billion bailout for farmers hurt by his trade war with Beijing, signaling a protracted fight ahead that is already prompting some American companies to shift business away from China.

abstract: Investors seemed to be reacting to a growing sense that the dispute between Washington and Beijing was deepening and would continue indefinitely.

lead_paragraph: Investors hunkered down Thursday, as signals from China and the United States suggested that both nations were girding for a long-term trade fight.
